From: Wei Chen <harperchen1110@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Mar 2023 07:18:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fbdev: nvidia: Fix potential divide by zero
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.1.23
Git-commit: 92e2a00f2987483e1f9253625828622edd442e61

[ Upstream commit 92e2a00f2987483e1f9253625828622edd442e61 ]

variable var->pixclock can be set by user. In case it
equals to zero, divide by zero would occur in nvidiafb_set_par.

Similar crashes have happened in other fbdev drivers. There
is no check and modification on var->pixclock along the call
chain to nvidia_check_var and nvidiafb_set_par. We believe it
could also be triggered in driver nvidia from user site.

Signed-off-by: Wei Chen <harperchen1110@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Helge Deller <deller@gmx.de>
Signed-off-by: Sasha Levin <sashal@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Robert Frohl <rfrohl@suse.com>
---
 drivers/video/fbdev/nvidia/nvidia.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/video/fbdev/nvidia/nvidia.c b/drivers/video/fbdev/nvidia/nvidia.c
index a6c3bc222246..1b8904824ad8 100644
--- a/drivers/video/fbdev/nvidia/nvidia.c
+++ b/drivers/video/fbdev/nvidia/nvidia.c
@@ -764,6 +764,8 @@ static int nvidiafb_check_var(struct fb_var_screeninfo *var,
 	int pitch, err = 0;
 
 	NVTRACE_ENTER();
+	if (!var->pixclock)
+		return -EINVAL;
 
 	var->transp.offset = 0;
 	var->transp.length = 0;
